table_caption: WMH volumes in patients with FTD compared with healthy controls
table_foot: Abbreviations: bvFTD: behavioral variant frontotemporal dementia; FTD, frontotemporal dementia; L, left; nfvPPA, nonfluent variant primary progressive aphasia; R, right; svPPA, semantic variant primary progressive aphasia; WM, white matter; WMH, white matter hyperintensity.aIndicates that there was a significant difference in the corresponding metric between the patient group and its matched healthy controls (p < 0.05); data represent median (25% fraction, 75% fraction).
